00:38:55,740 --> 00:38:58,860
Hey, want to grab a bite?

272
00:38:59,740 --> 00:39:01,820
Ama will be home soon.

273
00:39:01,950 --> 00:39:03,490
I see.

274
00:39:05,580 --> 00:39:06,910
See ya'.

275
00:39:40,110 --> 00:39:41,910
You okay?

276
00:39:55,300 --> 00:40:00,300
<i>I hate existing in this world. I want
to burn out in the realm of darkness.</i>

277
00:40:33,500 --> 00:40:35,000
<i>Our next news item...</i>

278
00:40:36,340 --> 00:40:40,590
<i>on 11th at 1:00am,
in Tokyo's Shibuya ward</i>

279
00:40:40,720 --> 00:40:45,340
<i>a man, bleeding from the head
was found by passersby.</i>

280
00:40:45,470 --> 00:40:49,640
<i>Although taken to hospital
he died 2 hours later.</i>

281
00:40:50,350 --> 00:40:57,270
<i>The deceased was a 25 year old
member of the Toryu yakuza group.</i>

282
00:40:57,520 --> 00:41:01,820
<i>Cerebral contusion following
skull fracture was the cause of death.</i>

283
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:05,870
<i>The fugitive suspect was described
as male in his mid 20's</i>

284
00:41:05,990 --> 00:41:09,700
<i>of medium height, slight build</i>

285
00:41:09,830 --> 00:41:14,670
<i>with red hair and dressed in dark clothing.</i>

286
00:41:15,710 --> 00:41:21,010
<i>The Shibuya precinct police
are searching for this suspect...</i>

287
00:41:33,890 --> 00:41:35,900
Good evening.

288
00:41:47,830 --> 00:41:50,490
Ama, get up.

289
00:41:50,660 --> 00:41:52,080
What's up?

290
00:41:52,700 --> 00:41:53,870
Come here.

291
00:41:54,080 --> 00:41:55,040
What?

292
00:41:56,080 --> 00:41:57,040
Quickly.

293
00:41:57,170 --> 00:41:58,250
What's going on?

294
00:41:58,380 --> 00:42:01,880
Nothing's going on. Sit down.

295
00:42:03,170 --> 00:42:05,010
We're dying your hair.

296
00:42:05,340 --> 00:42:09,600
I've never liked that ugly red hair.

297
00:42:09,930 --> 00:42:13,270
For starters, red looks scruffy on you.

298
00:42:13,600 --> 00:42:16,270
You've got no sense of taste.

299
00:42:19,020 --> 00:42:21,020
You're so good to me.

300
00:42:22,440 --> 00:42:27,610
I'll try to have good taste.
You'll help me, right?

301
00:42:28,530 --> 00:42:29,700
Of course.

302
00:42:45,550 --> 00:42:47,220
I'm grateful, y'know.

303
00:42:48,800 --> 00:42:51,760
I'd shave my head if you wanted.

304
00:42:52,140 --> 00:42:55,430
Dress up smart and fancy
like you.

305
00:42:55,890 --> 00:42:57,980
Bleach my skin if you told me.

306
00:43:00,730 --> 00:43:02,980
Give me a break.

307
00:43:07,240 --> 00:43:08,610
Ama...

308
00:43:10,320 --> 00:43:13,200
From tomorrow, my orders
are that you wear long sleeves.

309
00:43:13,330 --> 00:43:14,330
Why?

310
00:43:14,450 --> 00:43:18,790
Listen. The constant tank tops
make you look like a thug.

311
00:43:19,080 --> 00:43:20,580
Yes, Ma'am.

312
00:43:21,420 --> 00:43:22,340
Do you understand?

313
00:43:22,460 --> 00:43:24,050
I do.

314
00:43:24,170 --> 00:43:25,460
You promise?

315
00:43:25,590 --> 00:43:29,680
I promise. Anything for you, honey.

316
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:33,470
Quit it. That's creepy.

317
00:43:42,770 --> 00:43:44,520
Care for some more, sir?

318
00:43:45,280 --> 00:43:46,440
Thank you.

319
00:43:58,790 --> 00:44:00,960
What a shock...

320
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:03,960
A tongue stud, of all things...

321
00:44:05,300 --> 00:44:07,210
Some guy's involved, right?

322
00:44:07,460 --> 00:44:12,720
Kinda. I fell for the tongue
rather than the guy himself.

323
00:44:17,890 --> 00:44:19,060
Hello?

324
00:44:19,230 --> 00:44:22,810
<i>Lui, where are you?
What you doing?</i>

325
00:44:23,230 --> 00:44:26,730
Sorry. I got a call
for a companion gig.

326
00:44:26,860 --> 00:44:30,900
<i>What? I didn't know you worked.
What kind of "companion"?</i>

327
00:44:31,070 --> 00:44:36,870
For chrissakes, it's above board.
Nothing shady.

328
00:44:37,490 --> 00:44:40,580
Anyways, I'll call you later. Bye.

329
00:44:41,920 --> 00:44:43,210
Sorry.

330
00:44:43,500 --> 00:44:46,090
So he keeps you on a tight leash?

331
00:44:46,250 --> 00:44:51,380
He's like a big kid.
Sometimes he doesn't get it.

332
00:44:51,510 --> 00:44:53,510
That can be cute.

333
00:44:55,100 --> 00:44:57,390
If only that were all he is...

334
00:44:59,430 --> 00:45:03,440
There you are!
You mustn't goof off.

335
00:45:03,560 --> 00:45:04,730
Sorry, sir.

336
00:45:43,560 --> 00:45:46,980
Your hair looks better like this.

337
00:45:47,110 --> 00:45:48,650
Really?

338
00:45:49,230 --> 00:45:50,570
Looks cool.

339
00:45:51,320 --> 00:45:53,440
You reckon?

340
00:45:54,070 --> 00:45:56,570
You look good, too.

341
00:45:57,910 --> 00:45:58,990
I know.

342
00:45:59,160 --> 00:45:59,950
You do?

343
00:46:02,500 --> 00:46:05,540
Look... a split tongue.

344
00:46:06,920 --> 00:46:09,840
Oh, yeah. Split tongue.

345
00:46:13,920 --> 00:46:17,800
<i>Everything's okay. He's laughing
and happy.</i>

346
00:46:17,930 --> 00:46:23,850
<i>His hair's no longer red. We've
nothing to worry about. It's all fine.</i>

347
00:46:27,770 --> 00:46:29,610
I'm going to buy cigarettes.

348
00:46:44,290 --> 00:46:45,540
Hello.

349
00:46:45,660 --> 00:46:48,330
<i>It's me. The design's ready.</i>

350
00:46:49,130 --> 00:46:53,670
<i>A dragon and a kylin.
It was tough to get it right.</i>

351
00:46:53,800 --> 00:46:54,840
Really.

352
00:46:56,300 --> 00:46:58,050
<i>I want to show it to you.</i>

353
00:46:58,220 --> 00:46:59,510
Okay.

354
00:47:00,510 --> 00:47:01,640
<i>See ya', then.</i>

355
00:47:02,310 --> 00:47:03,390
See ya'.

356
00:47:06,640 --> 00:47:07,560
Who was that?

357
00:47:08,020 --> 00:47:11,440
Maki. She said we should party.

358
00:47:11,570 --> 00:47:13,230
Right, let's party...

359
00:47:18,660 --> 00:47:20,740
That's amazing.

360
00:47:20,910 --> 00:47:21,700
It's good, huh?

361
00:47:21,870 --> 00:47:22,870
Do this on me.

362
00:47:23,160 --> 00:47:24,080
Okay.

363
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:26,410
Isn't that great?

364
00:47:27,830 --> 00:47:29,750
No drinking alcohol tomorrow.

365
00:47:29,880 --> 00:47:33,290
And get a good sleep.
You'll need your strength.

366
00:47:33,420 --> 00:47:37,420
Don't worry. I'll look after her.

367
00:47:48,520 --> 00:47:52,690
Walking with you, everyone stares.

368
00:47:53,190 --> 00:47:54,770
You stand out more.

369
00:47:54,900 --> 00:47:56,110
What do you mean?

370
00:47:56,230 --> 00:47:58,610
You're both scary-looking.

371
00:47:59,700 --> 00:48:02,950
If you think about it,
we're a strange combination.

372
00:48:03,070 --> 00:48:06,080
I want a beer. Let's go eat.

373
00:48:06,620 --> 00:48:09,410
It changes when I breathe deep.

374
00:48:12,080 --> 00:48:13,290
It looks so cool.

375
00:48:14,130 --> 00:48:15,590
Sorry.

376
00:48:17,210 --> 00:48:19,470
I love this butterfly.

377
00:48:19,880 --> 00:48:20,720
It's good, huh?

378
00:48:20,840 --> 00:48:22,470
In the perfect place.

379
00:48:26,390 --> 00:48:27,720
I'm going to the toilet.

380
00:48:39,150 --> 00:48:41,150
No complaints about the design?

381
00:48:42,410 --> 00:48:43,820
Of course not.

382
00:48:45,580 --> 00:48:47,330
I'll make it so beautiful.

383
00:48:48,580 --> 00:48:52,460
In your hands,
it's a piece of cake, right?

384
00:48:56,250 --> 00:48:57,500
My divine hands...

385
00:49:09,430 --> 00:49:13,100
But what if I want to kill you
in the middle of it?

386
00:49:16,440 --> 00:49:19,360
If that's what happens, so be it.

387
00:49:22,110 --> 00:49:25,280
I've never wanted to kill anyone
so badly before.

388
00:49:28,120 --> 00:49:33,040
The toilet was covered in puke.
Made me feel sick.

389
00:49:33,210 --> 00:49:34,210
You threw up too, right?

390
00:49:34,330 --> 00:49:35,330
No, I didn't.

391
00:49:35,460 --> 00:49:37,380
Yeah, I bet you did.

392
00:49:37,500 --> 00:49:40,210
What are you talking about?

393
00:49:41,970 --> 00:49:43,300
Time for a toast.

394
00:49:43,470 --> 00:49:44,550
Cheers.

395
00:49:49,350 --> 00:49:50,890
Wow, it's so good.

396
00:49:55,150 --> 00:49:58,480
Shiba-san, this is tasty, too.

397
00:50:02,490 --> 00:50:05,860
<i>Amadeus, who beat
a man to death for me</i>

398
00:50:06,360 --> 00:50:09,370
<i>and the Descendant of God
who desperately wants to do me in.</i>

399
00:50:09,910 --> 00:50:13,910
<i>I wonder if one day
one of them will kill me.</i>

400
00:50:27,010 --> 00:50:29,180
Can I go with you tomorrow?

401
00:50:29,850 --> 00:50:33,770
What are you talking about?
You've got work.

402
00:50:37,690 --> 00:50:41,190
It's not that I don't trust Shiba-san...

403
00:50:43,280 --> 00:50:47,280
But I'm worried.
It'll just be you two, right?

404
00:50:52,870 --> 00:50:57,710
It'll be fine. He's a total pro.

405
00:50:58,210 --> 00:51:00,540
He wouldn't do anything like that.

406
00:51:02,550 --> 00:51:07,880
Okay. But be careful... really.

407
00:51:10,140 --> 00:51:15,810
Sometimes I don't understand
what goes through his mind.

408
00:51:23,900 --> 00:51:27,900
Not everyone's as easy
to understand as you.

409
00:51:49,340 --> 00:51:51,840
This time tomorrow,
there'll be a dragon here.

410
00:51:53,510 --> 00:51:54,970
And a <i>kylin</i>, too.

411
00:51:58,770 --> 00:52:03,770
Your skin's so perfectly white,
it's almost a shame.

412
00:52:06,360 --> 00:52:09,190
But with a tattoo,
you'll be even sexier.

413
00:52:22,170 --> 00:52:23,210
You had a proper sleep?

414
00:52:24,210 --> 00:52:27,460
Ama put me to bed by 8pm.

415
00:52:31,630 --> 00:52:33,220
Today we just do the outline.

416
00:52:35,470 --> 00:52:37,890
But it locks in the design

417
00:52:38,640 --> 00:52:40,560
so tell me if you want any changes.

418
00:52:43,650 --> 00:52:46,570
Just one request.

419
00:52:48,650 --> 00:52:52,240
I don't want you to do their eyes.

420
00:52:54,740 --> 00:52:56,530
You mean the actual pupil?

421
00:52:58,540 --> 00:53:02,660
Yeah, the eyeball itself.

422
00:53:04,750 --> 00:53:06,080
Why not?

423
00:53:07,250 --> 00:53:09,920
The old story of the priest
painting the dragon.

424
00:53:10,340 --> 00:53:13,340
He finished the eye
then it flew away.

425
00:53:22,270 --> 00:53:26,100
Okay, I see.

426
00:53:27,520 --> 00:53:29,780
I won't do their eyes then.

427
00:53:31,610 --> 00:53:36,110
But to keep their expressions
balanced

428
00:53:36,700 --> 00:53:39,620
I'll do a vague outline,
if that's okay?

429
00:53:40,540 --> 00:53:42,120
Thank you, Shiba-san.

430
00:53:44,370 --> 00:53:46,380
Such a demanding woman.

431
00:55:02,790 --> 00:55:03,870
How's that?

432
00:55:43,330 --> 00:55:44,660
Look.

433
00:55:47,500 --> 00:55:48,910
I used a gauge 10.

434
00:55:49,330 --> 00:55:51,750
That's coming along nicely.

435
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:55,920
But don't overdo it.

436
00:55:57,510 --> 00:56:00,760
Unlike an earlobe, an infected
tongue's a real nuisance.

437
00:56:02,100 --> 00:56:03,050
Okay.

438
00:56:07,770 --> 00:56:09,020
It hurt, right?

439
00:56:18,530 --> 00:56:19,860
Okay, I'm ready to begin.

440
00:56:23,280 --> 00:56:24,620
Here I go.

441
00:56:48,640 --> 00:56:50,100
Tell me if it hurts.

442
00:57:54,120 --> 00:57:56,460
You really don't mind
the pain, do you?

443
00:57:58,290 --> 00:58:01,710
First-timers usually bug me
with their whining.

444
00:58:04,470 --> 00:58:06,890
I guess I must be frigid.

445
00:58:07,050 --> 00:58:10,010
Hardly. You got off fine
the other day.

446
00:59:05,700 --> 00:59:07,450
You're sweet.

447
00:59:08,530 --> 00:59:09,780
The first drag's the best.

448
00:59:09,910 --> 00:59:13,410
No way. It's the second one.

449
00:59:18,540 --> 00:59:22,290
So, did you feel like killing me?

450
00:59:23,630 --> 00:59:28,090
Yes. So I kept my mind on the job.

451
00:59:37,730 --> 00:59:41,900
If you ever want to die
let me do the killing.

452
00:59:45,990 --> 00:59:47,610
Can I screw your corpse?

453
00:59:49,740 --> 00:59:53,160
After I'm dead, what do I care.

454
00:59:56,410 --> 01:00:01,000
Without your look of pain
I probably couldn't get it up.

455
01:01:59,700 --> 01:02:02,370
Lui... I'm here.

456
01:02:08,210 --> 01:02:09,540
We just finished.

457
01:02:11,050 --> 01:02:13,380
What about your job?

458
01:02:13,550 --> 01:02:16,050
Left early. Said I was constipated.

459
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:20,350
Your job lets you do that?

460
01:02:20,470 --> 01:02:23,140
The store manager was mad
but so what...

461
01:02:28,900 --> 01:02:31,070
Fantastic...

462
01:02:31,900 --> 01:02:33,900
Shiba-san, thank you.

463
01:02:35,820 --> 01:02:39,950
But you didn't try anything weird
with her, did you?

464
01:02:42,080 --> 01:02:46,500
Don't worry. I have no desire
for skinny women.

465
01:02:52,170 --> 01:02:53,000
Hang on...

466
01:02:57,090 --> 01:03:01,100
You didn't do their eyes.

467
01:03:02,520 --> 01:03:04,180
That's what I asked for.

468
01:03:05,680 --> 01:03:07,520
Not to complete the eyes.

469
01:03:07,650 --> 01:03:08,690
Why?

470
01:03:09,480 --> 01:03:12,770
They might fly away
after the finishing touch.

471
01:03:14,610 --> 01:03:16,440
I see.

472
01:03:18,110 --> 01:03:22,200
But my dragon's got eyes
and he's still here.

473
01:03:24,370 --> 01:03:26,540
- You keep quiet.
- Ouch. Don't hurt me...

474
01:03:27,330 --> 01:03:29,120
Don't have a bath for a while.

475
01:03:29,790 --> 01:03:34,050
It'll scab for about a week.
You mustn't scratch it.

476
01:03:34,960 --> 01:03:37,970
When the swelling's gone
we do the next session.

477
01:03:39,220 --> 01:03:42,720
In any case, call me
when the scabs come off.

478
01:03:46,480 --> 01:03:48,480
Shiba-san, want to go eat?

479
01:03:48,730 --> 01:03:51,150
Not at this time of day.

480
01:03:53,900 --> 01:03:57,900
Come over here.

481
01:03:58,700 --> 01:04:01,160
Why are you in a dress?

482
01:04:01,320 --> 01:04:03,740
You were just wearing your panties.

483
01:04:05,330 --> 01:04:09,660
I figured something loose
would be easier afterwards.

484
01:04:18,260 --> 01:04:19,880
Am I being pathetic?

485
01:04:22,430 --> 01:04:23,760
Kind of.

486
01:04:35,190 --> 01:04:37,030
You hate pathetic guys?

487
01:04:38,690 --> 01:04:39,940
Kind of.

488
01:04:44,580 --> 01:04:46,950
I'm so sorry.

489
01:04:48,120 --> 01:04:51,290
I guess you know already but,
I do love you.

490
01:05:15,060 --> 01:05:16,270
Let's go.

491
01:05:21,400 --> 01:05:25,660
<i>Then I went and got leglessly drunk.</i>

492
01:05:26,330 --> 01:05:29,450
<i>Ama was so happy to take care of me.</i>

493
01:05:29,750 --> 01:05:34,580
<i>It's a month after that "incident"
and Ama's still by my side.</i>

494
01:05:49,770 --> 01:05:54,640
<i>Each time I make it bigger
it hurts so bad, I don't want to go on.</i>

495
01:05:55,770 --> 01:05:57,860
<i>I vent my frustrations on Ama.</i>

496
01:05:58,110 --> 01:06:01,440
<i>On these days, I just feel
like I want everyone to die.</i>

497
01:06:02,110 --> 01:06:05,280
<i>Thoughts, values, all forgotten.
No better than a beast.</i>

498
01:07:35,750 --> 01:07:39,750
<i>When the irezumi
and the split tongue are done</i>

499
01:07:40,080 --> 01:07:42,750
<i>how am I going to feel, I wonder?</i>

500
01:07:43,800 --> 01:07:48,630
<i>I've lived life not owning much,
worrying little, caring less.</i>

501
01:07:49,970 --> 01:07:56,310
<i>No meaning anywhere. Not in
the future, the tattoo or this tongue.</i>

502
01:09:14,510 --> 01:09:16,550
Maybe I'll quit being a tattooist.

503
01:09:20,390 --> 01:09:23,850
Like Ama, try sticking with one woman.

504
01:09:26,060 --> 01:09:29,030
What's that got to do with quitting?

505
01:09:29,860 --> 01:09:32,070
The "making a new start" thing.

506
01:09:34,410 --> 01:09:36,530
I created my best ever <i>kylin</i>.

507
01:09:40,910 --> 01:09:44,040
So I'd have no regrets.

508
01:09:51,840 --> 01:09:57,510
<i>The beasts dancing on my back
will never leave me.</i>

509
01:09:58,430 --> 01:10:04,100
<i>We are locked together,
unable to betray or be betrayed.</i>

510
01:10:04,900 --> 01:10:08,900
<i>And without eyes, they can't escape.</i>

511
01:10:16,410 --> 01:10:22,120
<i>Maybe because the tattoo is done,
I'm sapped of all energy.</i>

512
01:10:22,790 --> 01:10:26,000
<i>I spend each day wishing time faster.</i>

513
01:10:26,120 --> 01:10:28,130
- You mustn't drink.
- Get lost.

514
01:10:29,420 --> 01:10:32,920
<i>Ama worries about me
and my constant drinking</i>

515
01:10:33,130 --> 01:10:36,130
<i>and I want to respond to him</i>

516
01:10:36,800 --> 01:10:42,140
<i>but defeated by self-loathing
I just turn back to the booze.</i>

517
01:10:43,140 --> 01:10:45,600
<i>Anyway, my life is devoid of light.</i>

518
01:10:46,230 --> 01:10:51,440
<i>Inside my head, my life, my future
nothing but total darkness.</i>

519
01:10:53,400 --> 01:10:58,990
<i>The only time I really feel alive
is when I'm in pain.</i>

520
01:11:02,290 --> 01:11:06,750
Ever feel like you want to die?

521
01:11:10,840 --> 01:11:12,670
All the time.

522
01:11:19,680 --> 01:11:26,180
I won't stand for anyone taking
your life. Not even you yourself.

523
01:11:30,980 --> 01:11:34,650
If you're going to kill yourself,
let me be the one to do it.

524
01:11:40,200 --> 01:11:42,370
I couldn't bear it...

525
01:11:43,870 --> 01:11:49,540
the thought of anyone but me
having control over your life.

526
01:11:56,550 --> 01:12:01,720
<i>When the need to die possesses me
who will I ask to kill me?</i>

527
01:12:02,800 --> 01:12:06,220
<i>Who would make the best job of it?</i>

528
01:12:31,580 --> 01:12:34,840
<i>It's me. Can you talk?</i>

529
01:12:35,420 --> 01:12:38,340
