show my client list.

536
01:13:05,080 --> 01:13:07,620
Wanted to know about
a dragon tattoo.

537
01:13:09,910 --> 01:13:11,960
I don't think it's Ama but...

538
01:13:12,460 --> 01:13:16,750
<i>It can't be him. He was
always with me.</i>

539
01:13:18,090 --> 01:13:21,090
That's what I thought.

540
01:13:24,800 --> 01:13:29,970
They mentioned red hair.
Remember, it used to be red?

541
01:13:31,270 --> 01:13:32,730
So I was a bit worried.

542
01:13:34,150 --> 01:13:35,150
Oh...

543
01:13:46,660 --> 01:13:49,160
I just thought I'd call to check.

544
01:13:51,000 --> 01:13:52,080
Coming over, today?

545
01:13:53,000 --> 01:13:56,290
Oh... thanks.

546
01:13:57,000 --> 01:14:01,460
Not today. But next time.

547
01:14:01,630 --> 01:14:07,470
Won't you please come?
I need to talk to you.

548
01:14:11,680 --> 01:14:13,980
Okay... if I get in the mood.

549
01:15:15,000 --> 01:15:16,000
Good afternoon.

550
01:15:16,710 --> 01:15:18,580
You're being formal.

551
01:15:25,380 --> 01:15:26,420
Are you tired?

552
01:15:37,100 --> 01:15:39,230
I'm not joking... something's wrong.

553
01:15:39,770 --> 01:15:41,270
What is?

554
01:15:42,940 --> 01:15:44,940
When did we last meet?

555
01:15:47,950 --> 01:15:50,240
Maybe 2 weeks ago?

556
01:15:50,780 --> 01:15:52,660
How much weight did you lose?

557
01:15:52,780 --> 01:15:56,580
No idea. Ama doesn't have scales.

558
01:15:58,080 --> 01:16:00,420
It's creepy how skinny you got.

559
01:16:01,790 --> 01:16:05,750
You're really pale.
You stink of booze.

560
01:16:22,150 --> 01:16:24,320
Isn't Ama feeding you properly?

561
01:16:25,480 --> 01:16:28,490
He's always nagging me to eat.

562
01:16:29,320 --> 01:16:32,450
All I need is alcohol though.

563
01:16:33,120 --> 01:16:37,120
You'll starve before you get
to commit suicide.

564
01:16:38,460 --> 01:16:40,460
I won't commit suicide.

565
01:16:47,010 --> 01:16:50,630
I'm going to buy something.
What do you want?

566
01:16:51,470 --> 01:16:53,470
A beer, then.

567
01:16:54,470 --> 01:16:58,810
Beer's in the fridge. Anything else?

568
01:17:01,140 --> 01:17:06,860
Shiba-san, ever killed someone?

569
01:17:22,210 --> 01:17:23,500
Yeah, I have...

570
01:17:30,840 --> 01:17:32,840
How did you feel?

571
01:17:38,680 --> 01:17:40,220
I felt great.

572
01:17:45,400 --> 01:17:46,900
Yeah?

573
01:18:00,410 --> 01:18:01,910
Take off your clothes.

574
01:18:04,580 --> 01:18:07,210
Not going shopping?

575
01:18:10,380 --> 01:18:12,590
Seeing you cry made me hard.

576
01:19:27,830 --> 01:19:29,670
Will you marry me?

577
01:19:31,840 --> 01:19:34,550
That's why you wanted to talk?

578
01:19:34,670 --> 01:19:35,920
I guess.

579
01:19:39,140 --> 01:19:42,810
Ama's too much for you to handle.

580
01:19:44,520 --> 01:19:47,480
And you're too much for him.

581
01:19:47,690 --> 01:19:49,980
You're not a good match
for each other.

582
01:19:51,820 --> 01:19:54,360
So I have to marry you?

583
01:19:54,480 --> 01:19:59,030
That's nothing to do with it.

584
01:19:59,860 --> 01:20:02,030
I just felt like getting married.

585
01:20:26,350 --> 01:20:28,230
In any case I made a ring.

586
01:20:33,570 --> 01:20:35,070
You made this?

587
01:20:35,530 --> 01:20:37,530
It's a hobby of mine.

588
01:20:39,070 --> 01:20:42,070
Probably not your style at all...

589
01:20:44,530 --> 01:20:45,870
It's amazing.

590
01:20:47,830 --> 01:20:49,910
But kind of grim-looking.

591
01:20:56,550 --> 01:20:57,880
Thank you.

592
01:21:04,930 --> 01:21:06,430
I'm going shopping.

593
01:22:32,850 --> 01:22:36,650
<i>The number you called
may not be in the service area</i>

594
01:22:36,770 --> 01:22:39,820
<i>or may be turned off.
Your call cannot be completed.</i>

595
01:23:30,870 --> 01:23:32,330
Excuse me.

596
01:23:33,540 --> 01:23:36,250
Can a non-relative report
a missing person?

597
01:23:36,410 --> 01:23:37,870
Yeah, they can.

598
01:23:39,040 --> 01:23:40,210
Want to?

599
01:23:41,710 --> 01:23:42,710
I do.

600
01:23:43,590 --> 01:23:44,590
Their name?

601
01:24:01,560 --> 01:24:04,110
<i>I don't know his real name.</i>

602
01:24:04,900 --> 01:24:09,570
<i>Not knowing his name, I can't even
file a missing person report.</i>

603
01:24:21,250 --> 01:24:23,130
What's Ama's real name?

604
01:24:24,590 --> 01:24:26,090
Why, all of a sudden?

605
01:24:28,550 --> 01:24:32,140
He didn't come home.
I want to report him missing.

606
01:24:32,760 --> 01:24:37,100
What? You don't know his name?

607
01:24:37,930 --> 01:24:39,270
No, I don't.

608
01:24:39,560 --> 01:24:40,980
You're living together, right?

609
01:24:41,100 --> 01:24:42,980
Yes, of course...

610
01:24:44,610 --> 01:24:46,270
Stop crying.

611
01:24:49,900 --> 01:24:53,410
Look at his mailbox
or at his letters.

612
01:24:54,120 --> 01:24:57,620
He didn't put his name on it.

613
01:24:57,950 --> 01:25:02,330
And it's stuffed full of flyers.
We never even opened it.

614
01:25:02,790 --> 01:25:05,090
He went to work
as usual yesterday, right?

615
01:25:06,750 --> 01:25:09,170
So he didn't come back last night?

616
01:25:09,300 --> 01:25:13,180
Right. He didn't come home
since leaving for work.

617
01:25:13,970 --> 01:25:17,760
Why lose your head over 1 day?

618
01:25:18,140 --> 01:25:19,930
Nothing to worry about.

619
01:25:21,640 --> 01:25:26,360
Don't get in a panic
about a single day. He's not a child.

620
01:25:26,650 --> 01:25:31,030
Since living together, he's never once
stayed away from home.

621
01:25:31,200 --> 01:25:34,870
He's the kind of guy who calls
if he's 30 minutes late.

622
01:25:35,660 --> 01:25:36,830
So what...

623
01:25:40,500 --> 01:25:42,790
He might've killed someone.

624
01:25:45,840 --> 01:25:49,170
That gangster the police mentioned?

625
01:25:49,300 --> 01:25:51,050
It was my fault.

626
01:25:51,340 --> 01:25:55,680
If I'd ignored that guy
he wouldn't have punched him.

627
01:25:56,510 --> 01:25:59,180
I never thought anyone would die.

628
01:26:00,180 --> 01:26:05,020
Even on the news, I never thought
it was the same guy.

629
01:26:06,690 --> 01:26:08,900
I figured it was someone else for sure.

630
01:26:09,070 --> 01:26:10,900
Nothing to do with Ama...

631
01:26:15,870 --> 01:26:19,870
If you file a report, he might be arrested.

632
01:26:22,710 --> 01:26:26,540
If he's on the run 'cause of the fight

633
01:26:29,050 --> 01:26:32,420
and we just play dumb,
he might be able to make it.

634
01:26:32,590 --> 01:26:34,930
But I'm worried about him.

635
01:26:37,350 --> 01:26:41,560
It kills me not to know where he is.

636
01:26:44,060 --> 01:26:48,730
He wouldn't try to run away by himself.

637
01:26:50,020 --> 01:26:53,280
He'd talk to me, for sure.

638
01:26:53,740 --> 01:26:57,280
I'm sure he'd ask me to go with him.

639
01:27:03,250 --> 01:27:04,540
I understand.

640
01:27:06,750 --> 01:27:07,920
Let's go.

641
01:27:21,930 --> 01:27:24,100
So you had a picture of him?

642
01:27:26,940 --> 01:27:30,980
We got carried away when I did the tattoo.

643
01:27:31,270 --> 01:27:34,780
Mr. Kazunori Amada, right?

644
01:27:44,620 --> 01:27:47,250
Not Amadeus, at all...

645
01:27:52,630 --> 01:27:54,590
Are you okay?

646
01:28:49,480 --> 01:28:51,730
Where the hell are you?

647
01:28:55,020 --> 01:28:57,900
Why did you leave me?

648
01:29:09,830 --> 01:29:13,080
How come you disappeared?

649
01:29:16,340 --> 01:29:19,670
You said you cared for me.

650
01:29:22,680 --> 01:29:26,260
Then why'd you leave me behind?

651
01:29:28,850 --> 01:29:33,940
Why... why?

652
01:29:59,380 --> 01:30:00,420
What are you doing?

653
01:30:02,380 --> 01:30:03,550
Show me your tongue.

654
01:30:04,890 --> 01:30:09,310
That's a 0 gauge, right?
Yesterday you only had a 4...

655
01:30:11,270 --> 01:30:12,270
Stop it.

656
01:30:17,650 --> 01:30:18,610
Take it out.

657
01:30:25,320 --> 01:30:27,660
I said don't overdo it, right?

658
01:30:38,960 --> 01:30:41,920
When I'm at 00, I'm cutting it.

659
01:30:42,760 --> 01:30:46,590
Okay, I get it. Calm down.

660
01:30:51,680 --> 01:30:53,480
Ama...

661
01:30:54,770 --> 01:30:59,270
What would he say if he saw it?

662
01:31:02,860 --> 01:31:04,990
"Wow, that's amazing"

663
01:31:07,620 --> 01:31:10,620
and he'd laugh...

664
01:31:12,700 --> 01:31:15,370
"Nearly there"...

665
01:31:17,630 --> 01:31:19,040
That's what he'd say...

666
01:31:21,800 --> 01:31:23,380
I know it...

667
01:31:27,470 --> 01:31:29,550
He'd be happy for me.

668
01:31:42,900 --> 01:31:46,570
<i>The number you called
may not be in the service area</i>

669
01:31:46,820 --> 01:31:49,570
<i>or may be turned off.
Your call cannot be completed.</i>

670
01:32:01,340 --> 01:32:03,590
You know where Ama works?

671
01:32:04,920 --> 01:32:06,050
Don't you know?

672
01:32:06,340 --> 01:32:07,840
No, I don't.

673
01:32:11,430 --> 01:32:13,390
We don't know much about each other.

674
01:32:15,930 --> 01:32:17,390
A vintage clothing store.

675
01:32:18,690 --> 01:32:21,100
You really don't know anything.

676
01:32:23,440 --> 01:32:25,570
So you didn't call them yet?

677
01:32:43,380 --> 01:32:46,710
It's me. I'm calling about Ama.

678
01:32:50,470 --> 01:32:54,430
Skipped work? What about yesterday?

679
01:32:56,560 --> 01:32:58,770
I'll call if I find out anything.

680
01:33:06,320 --> 01:33:08,990
They say he turned up for work
as usual, yesterday.

681
01:33:11,240 --> 01:33:13,320
Today, he skipped work.

682
01:33:15,120 --> 01:33:17,660
They were angry he hadn't called.

683
01:33:20,830 --> 01:33:24,670
He works at my friend's store.

684
01:33:27,090 --> 01:33:29,590
I had to beg them to employ him.

685
01:33:33,930 --> 01:33:36,260
Has Ama got any family?

686
01:33:39,180 --> 01:33:40,480
I don't know.

687
01:33:42,270 --> 01:33:44,150
I think he might have one parent.

688
01:33:45,610 --> 01:33:49,940
He mentioned a father once, I think.

689
01:33:50,440 --> 01:33:51,780
Oh...

690
01:34:15,340 --> 01:34:19,470
Jesus. Nothing but booze.

691
01:34:23,060 --> 01:34:24,230
Phone's ringing.

692
01:34:37,320 --> 01:34:39,200
Yes, I understand.

693
01:34:57,680 --> 01:35:00,180
They found a body in the suburbs.

694
01:35:02,020 --> 01:35:07,400
They don't know if it's him
but there's a dragon on the body.

695
01:35:12,610 --> 01:35:15,570
They want us at the morgue
to identify it.

696
01:36:16,590 --> 01:36:18,170
<i>Ama is dead.</i>

697
01:36:18,300 --> 01:36:21,180
<i>Asphyxiation by strangulation.</i>

698
01:36:21,930 --> 01:36:25,520
<i>His body covered in cigarette burns.</i>

699
01:36:26,520 --> 01:36:30,190
<i>All his nails cleanly plucked off.</i>

700
01:36:30,520 --> 01:36:33,690
<i>Something like an incense stick
stuck in his penis.</i>

701
01:36:34,780 --> 01:36:40,320
<i>It's like they had their fill of sport
before killing him.</i>

702
01:36:40,950 --> 01:36:47,620
<i>The body I regarded as my own
possession, trifled with and killed...</i>

703
01:36:49,960 --> 01:36:52,460
I'm off then, Lui.

704
01:36:54,800 --> 01:37:00,380
<i>The last time we spoke
I practically ignored him</i>

705
01:37:00,510 --> 01:37:03,050
<i>as I thought about
going to see Shiba-san.</i>

706
01:37:03,180 --> 01:37:04,970
See you later.

707
01:37:41,340 --> 01:37:43,590
When will you find the killer?

708
01:37:43,720 --> 01:37:46,260
We're making a full investigation.

709
01:37:46,510 --> 01:37:50,020
Huh? You think I'm out of line?

710
01:37:50,930 --> 01:37:55,730
At the funeral but you didn't catch
the guy, how come?

711
01:37:55,860 --> 01:37:58,860
You think I'm a pain-in-the-ass?

712
01:37:59,280 --> 01:38:02,280
You've no authority anyway.

713
01:38:02,610 --> 01:38:07,410
So what? Is it pushy of me
to demand that you catch him?

714
01:38:08,200 --> 01:38:11,790
You're not trying 'cause Ama
killed someone, right?

715
01:38:12,210 --> 01:38:18,460
You all fuck off and die.
That'd be a big help.

716
01:38:18,590 --> 01:38:21,130
Behave, Lui. You're just ranting.

717
01:38:21,260 --> 01:38:24,430
Fuck off. You jerks can all die.

718
01:38:56,580 --> 01:38:58,830
Let's just hang out in the store.

719
01:39:00,000 --> 01:39:03,670
The doctor said take it easy, right?

720
01:39:30,620 --> 01:39:34,790
<i>After moving out of Ama's place
and living with Shiba-san</i>

721
01:39:35,790 --> 01:39:40,460
<i>he tried so many times to make love
to me, but he couldn't...</i>

722
01:39:41,840 --> 01:39:46,970
<i>because I didn't make that look of pain
even when he throttled me.</i>

723
01:40:03,900 --> 01:40:05,570
Shiba-san...

724
01:40:07,820 --> 01:40:11,820
Won't you stop putting -san on my name?

725
01:40:14,330 --> 01:40:16,660
My name is Kizuki Shibata.

726
01:40:18,330 --> 01:40:20,080
Sounds like a woman's name, right?

727
01:40:23,340 --> 01:40:26,760
Don't know why but everyone
calls me, Shiba.

728
01:40:29,010 --> 01:40:30,680
What should I call you?

729
01:40:30,840 --> 01:40:32,350
Kizuki will do.

730
01:40:37,270 --> 01:40:38,390
What?

731
01:40:39,520 --> 01:40:42,440
It's full... no space for more.

732
01:40:44,940 --> 01:40:46,440
Just cram them in.

733
01:40:55,290 --> 01:40:59,250
Lui, can I ask your name?

734
01:41:00,460 --> 01:41:01,790
You want to know?

735
01:41:01,920 --> 01:41:03,750
I'm asking 'cause I want to know.

736
01:41:06,210 --> 01:41:07,960
Lui, as in "Louis Vuitton"...

737
01:41:08,130 --> 01:41:10,260
Your real name.

738
01:41:12,140 --> 01:41:14,100
Lui Nakazawa.

739
01:41:15,470 --> 01:41:17,930
So Lui is your real name...

740
01:41:20,890 --> 01:41:25,310
Lui, you got family... parents?

741
01:41:27,400 --> 01:41:32,070
People think I'm an orphan
but my parents are around.

742
01:41:33,160 --> 01:41:36,120
In the suburbs somewhere, I guess.

743
01:41:38,500 --> 01:41:39,660
Not what I expected.

744
01:41:41,420 --> 01:41:43,580
I should go introduce myself.

745
01:41:48,420 --> 01:41:54,590
Ama and I never got to talk like this.

746
01:41:58,270 --> 01:42:02,600
Wish I'd had normal conversations
with him.

747
01:42:03,690 --> 01:42:06,190
About family...

748
01:42:08,280 --> 01:42:12,610
about names and ages...

749
01:42:15,120 --> 01:42:21,450
I first heard he was 18 at the funeral.

750
01:42:24,790 --> 01:42:31,300
For the first time in my life
dating a guy younger than me...

751
01:42:32,800 --> 01:42:35,630
then only finding out after he died.

752
01:42:37,300 --> 01:42:41,140
The sort of thing we should've
talked about when we met.

753
01:42:56,450 --> 01:43:04,210
The cigarettes stubbed on his body
were all "Marlboro Menthol".

754
01:43:04,710 --> 01:43:07,540
Saliva analysis is still underway.

755
01:43:12,880 --> 01:43:19,550
The incense inserted into his privates

756
01:43:20,760 --> 01:43:25,350
"Extasy" brand imported from America,
Musk scented...

757
01:43:25,890 --> 01:43:28,400
Incense is sold everywhere.

758
01:43:28,900 --> 01:43:34,280
Well, yes.
Mainly the Eastern regions...

759
01:43:40,740 --> 01:43:45,450
Also, there's one thing we'd like
to ask you, Ms. Nakazawa.

760
01:43:48,750 --> 01:43:55,130
Was there any indication
of Mr. Amada being bisexual?

761
01:43:56,970 --> 01:44:00,090
You're saying he was raped as well?

762
01:44:03,770 --> 01:44:06,640
It was discovered at the autopsy.

763
01:44:09,650 --> 01:44:13,270
There was no sign of that. I swear.

764
01:44:13,400 --> 01:44:15,940
He wasn't that way inclined.

765
01:44:17,950 --> 01:44:19,610
Is that right?

766
01:45:03,490 --> 01:45:05,490
Zero progress.

767
01:45:06,370 --> 01:45:07,660
Really...

768
01:45:46,530 --> 01:45:48,200
Take a rest.

769
01:46:46,090 --> 01:46:48,600
Where did you go?
I was worried.

770
01:46:50,600 --> 01:46:54,940
I bought some incense. I hate musk.

771
01:46:59,610 --> 01:47:01,610
I got coconut.

772
01:47:21,170 --> 01:47:22,500
What's the problem?

773
01:47:22,840 --> 01:47:24,340
Nothing.

774
01:47:24,470 --> 01:47:29,140
Hey, Kizuki. Why not grow your hair?
I love long hair.

775
01:47:30,680 --> 01:47:34,680
Maybe. It's worth trying some time.

776
01:51:17,570 --> 01:51:23,580
<i>The proof of Ama's love
dissolves and becomes part of me.</i>

777
01:51:53,230 --> 01:51:58,070
Kizuki, I've got a favor to ask.

778
01:51:58,410 --> 01:51:59,570
What?

779
01:52:05,290 --> 01:52:06,540
You're sure it's okay?

780
01:52:22,100 --> 01:52:23,060
Here we go.

781
01:53:02,350 --> 01:53:06,680
<i>Now I can be sure
that the tattoo finally means something.</i>

782
01:53:07,350 --> 01:53:13,310
<i>I had the eyes drawn
so that I myself might have life.</i>

783
01:53:13,820 --> 01:53:15,360
Will they fly away?

784
01:53:16,190 --> 01:53:18,030
They just might do that.

785
01:53:39,220 --> 01:53:43,840
<i>Everything's fine. Even if
Shiba-san was the one who killed Ama.</i>

786
01:53:44,010 --> 01:53:48,350
<i>Even if he was the one
who raped Ama. It's fine.</i>

787
01:56:25,300 --> 01:56:27,970
<i>Is this really what I was after?</i>

788
01:56:28,180 --> 01:56:32,010
<i>Was this ugly, gaping hole
really what I was chasing?</i>

789
01:57:41,420 --> 01:57:42,790
What are you doing?

790
01:57:44,750 --> 01:57:46,960
There's a river inside me.

791
01:57:54,970 --> 01:57:56,640
I just had the strangest dream.

792
01:57:58,270 --> 01:57:59,640
What about?

793
01:58:03,150 --> 01:58:06,440
I was supposed to hang out
with a bunch of old friends.

794
01:58:08,280 --> 01:58:11,320
But I turned up really late.

795
01:58:13,110 --> 01:58:19,290
They showed their anger
by singing at me.

796
01:58:22,790 --> 01:58:28,130
Me, surrounded by 5 or 6 of them
as they sang... a song of anger.

797
01:58:35,140 --> 01:58:41,310
<i>When I put in the 00 gauge
will the river flow full flood?</i>
